# Python
# Bytecode files
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyd
*.pyo

# Virtual environment
# You might use venv, .venv, env, or something else.
# Add any directories where your virtual environment is stored.
venv/
.venv/
env/

# Flask specific (example database file)
# If you are using SQLAlchemy with a file-based DB (like SQLite)
# and don't want to commit the actual DB file.
# Adjust the filename if yours is different.
app.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# Sensitive configuration files
# Be cautious ignoring config files. It's often better to use
# environment variables or ignore only local/sensitive versions,
# not the base configuration template.
# Example: a file named `config_local.py` or a .env file
config*.py  # Potentially too broad, use with care and adjust
.env
*.env

# IDE and editor files
# Ignore project/workspace files from your IDE or editor
.idea/          # JetBrains (PyCharm, etc.)
.vscode/        # VS Code (Optional - sometimes contains useful launch configs.
                # Consider if you want to commit specific debug settings)
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace

# Operating System files
.DS_Store       # macOS
Thumbs.db       # Windows

# Logs
*.log

